@node Installation "Gaussian Blur: Installation"

                                  Installation
                                 --------------

- copy the files from drawer plugins2/ to ArtEffect:plugins2/

- copy the Guide whereever you can retrieve it.

After the next start of ArtEffect2+ the menuentry "Gaussian Blur VR..." should
be available in Menu Filter/Blur.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Gaussian Blur: Requirements"

                                  Requirements
                                 --------------

- the only thing you need is ArtEffect2+

@endnode

@node Usage "Gaussian Blur: Usage"

                                     Usage
                                    -------

   The usage is quite easy, after calling the plugin via menu, you will see a
   little window.

   Just below the preview is a cycle gadget to select wether the plugin should
   work in color, grayscale or blur the @{" Alphachannel " link Alphachannel}. Operating in grayscale is
   faster and will convert the picture to gray on-the-fly.

   Radius is the radius around every pixel that will be taken into calculation
   for the actual calculated pixel. E.g. for a Radius of 10 the Matrix has a
   size of 21x21 pixels and is taking 441 surrounding pixels into calculation.
   The higher the Radius is the blurrier the picture gets.

   Finetune can be used to reduce the effect. Tecnically speaken it narrows the
   gaussian curve.

@endnode

@node Alphachannel "Gaussian Blur: Alphachannel"

                                  Alphachannel
                                 --------------

   In Alphachannel-mode the mask/stencil of the picture is blurred. It can be
   used as different approach to get smooth borders in your mask.

   The effect can be a fast and better replacement for ArtEffect's
   Stencil/Feather, but have to be used a little different. Feather creates a
   smooth border around the selection, the selection grows and pixels of the
   former selection are not changed. Gaussian Blur blurs the selection and so
   changes also some of the former selection pixels.

   To come close the original feather function use stencil/grow first and then
   Gaussian Blur.
   Short: Feather 10 = Grow 5 + Blur 5


   There are some unhandsome things:

   - Working on the alphachannel is not undoable in ArtEffect3.

   - The stencil in preview has to be calculated by the plugin and AE does not
     which color is used as stencil color. So the stencil is always displayed
     as red (AEs default stencil color) in the preview.

@endnode

@node Notes "Gaussian Blur: Notes"

                                     Notes
                                    -------

 - Gaussian Blur was written on an Amiga 4000 with Cyberstorm MK1 060 and
   compiled with SAS/C 6.58.

 - This PlugIn has no AREXX-Interface and is not localized nor the documentation
   is available in any other language than english (or whatever this is here).
   That may or may not change in the future.

 - If you are interested in getting the information how long an operation took
   try this: setenv VRPLUGINTIMING 1
   

@endnode

@node History "Gaussian Blur: History"

                                    History
                                   ---------
V1.1

- added: New colormode, that blurs the alphachannel. Please read the
